The paper presents a new algorithm for unsupervised learning, specifically for canonical correlation analysis (CCA) with feature selection. This is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the algorithm for image data (cs.CV) and large-scale/streaming data (cs.ST), indicating that it may be relevant to those sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves optimization and iterative approaches, which are topics that fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
